people who seem really happy with those systems are guilds who generally don't fight over loot in the first place.  Class reps and a well-defined chain of command work wonders, use them.  <br>Second, while racing to equip one person in whatever gear may push them over the sweet spot where their AC is greater than &lt;ubermob&gt;'s ATK, this doesn't happen very often.  It may happen if you are a new guild, made up of people in mid-level quest armor, but you will probably ramp up to these mobs anyway, and not just start off fighting them.  Equip all your tanks equally, and they'll all hit that sweet spot about the same time, and you might actually be able to kill the mob even if your main tank dies.  (Oh no, &lt;warrior_01&gt; down, now &lt;warrior_02&gt;, &lt;warrior_03&gt;, and &lt;warrior_04&gt; are down too.  We got a campout cleric?)<br>Third, if you're a new guild starting up, or an existing guild gearing up to do end-game encounters, expect to lose several of your better equipped folks to larger, more mature guilds.  It happens, especially if they're much better equipped than the rest of the guild.  Don't take it personally, don't hate the person or their new guild, don't let an in-game incident affect real-life friendships.<br>Fourth, Extreme's language in this post may be interpreted to be referring to a certain person in our guild.  I certainly don't think that is the case.  I've known Extreme for many, many years, and the phrase is one that he uses constantly.  I'm sure it was not intended to indicate anyone in particular.  <br>Finally, how can getting your epic or whatever piece of gear be an ending point?  Maybe I'm just weird, but I've been looking forward for my epic for so long because I know that it will make me more effective, making my groups more effective, making my guild more effective, making it easier to kill big mobs.  (OK, granted, bard epics are actually useful, and even the uberest of the uber bards still use them as off-hand weapons, unlike some other epics.)  I can see how you could burn out because you've killed all the interesting mobs in the game, but how many people in a guild that can awaken the Sleeper aren't epic?<br>Anyway, just the ramblings of a bard who still loves the game as much as ever.  Of course once I hit 60 I'll burn out and start playing my twink warrior full-time....NOT!<br><br>Arolpin<br>finally with blue notes<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uirongut.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Irongut</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/17/02 11:42:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=216.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://irongut.dnsip.net/irongut/gutface.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Lessons learned from MA equipping a large guild</span><hr size=1> We give loot based on who will look the most silly with it.<br><br>There are few things as fun as mocking someone with bright green pants. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/utjark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tjark</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/17/02 11:43:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=216.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   HRMMM</span><hr size=1> ^------  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uatrian.showPublicProfile?languag